 the scoop.\n\n#oott #iran https://t.co/70c95EUBTd", "time": "02:03", "author": "CRUDEOIL231", "author_name": "JH", "followers": 58936, "views": 19798, "likes": 199, "replies": 6, "retweets": 22, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 5, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063825868137411072", "url": "https://x.com/business/status/2063825868137411011", "text": "Reopening the Strait of Hormuz would flood the world with oil much faster than many people expect, argues @JavierBlas #OOTT (via @opinion)  https://t.co/ufArRfvC3E", "time": "03:30", "author": "business", "author_name": "Bloomberg", "followers": 10174305, "views": 27291, "likes": 137, "replies": 21, "retweets": 38, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 20, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063856288799326510", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2063856288799326510", "text": "101 days. \n\nIsrael and Iran are trading fire, with several rounds overnight of attacks. The latest strikes follow an escalation between Israel and Hezbollah. President Trump urged Israel to show restraint. \n\nOil is up ~4% but remains below $100 a barrel.", "time": "05:30", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 29621, "likes": 224, "replies": 23, "retweets": 40, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 15, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063889039233601948", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2063889039233601948", "text": "COLUMN: When the day comes, the reopening of the Strait of Hormuz will be extraordinary: restarting about 10,000 oil wells, pumping roughly 15% of the world’s production.\n\nWhen it happens, it would go quicker than many think: weeks, not months.\n\n@Opinion\nhttps://t.co/oav02e1Rdk", "time": "07:41", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 112805, "likes": 649, "replies": 137, "retweets": 139, "quotes": 29, "bookmarks": 146, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063902486776147983", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2063902486776147983", "text": "As always, @glcarlstrom providing some key nuance:", "time": "08:34", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 47586, "likes": 66, "replies": 5, "retweets": 5, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063920340049313880", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2063920340049313880", "text": "One is an ally; the other is a foe. Which makes President Trump’s demand even more interesting. https://t.co/OItAODgOFo", "time": "09:45", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 37689, "likes": 165, "replies": 29, "retweets": 19, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 6, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063929137341817022", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2063929137341817022", "text": "UAE state owned oil company ADNOC has awarded a tender for ~14 million barrels of crude, and it’s planning a 2nd tender. The sales are a further indication that significant volumes of crude are exiting the Strait of Hormuz in small vessels going dark (AIS beacon off).", "time": "10:20", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 439974, "likes": 1040, "replies": 53, "retweets": 192, "quotes": 30, "bookmarks": 140, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063944442726281260", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2063944442726281260", "text": "BREAKING: Iran declares end of military operations against Israel, according to the semi-official Fars news agency.", "time": "11:21", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 164678, "likes": 499, "replies": 30, "retweets": 75, "quotes": 16, "bookmarks": 17, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063971387916931072", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2063971387916931256", "text": "Crossings through the monitored Strait of Hormuz zone remained low over 5–7 June, with only 8  total transits across commercial and non-commercial traffic. @Kpler #OOTT", "time": "13:08", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 173868, "views": 21113, "likes": 117, "replies": 8, "retweets": 20, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 6, "labels": null}, {"id": "2063971740871541056", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2063971740871541056", "text": "CHART OF THE DAY: At least some positive news to follow the US-Iran conflict. The price of Arabica coffee has plunged to a mear 2-year low on expectations of a large harvest in Brazil. Considering my war-watching high caffeine consumption, that's very good news. https://t.co/lnzO9nIgoS", "time": "13:09", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 20767, "likes": 218, "replies": 12, "retweets": 24, "quotes": 4, "bookmarks": 8, "labels": null}, {"id": "2064004710877556992", "url": "https://x.com/OilandEnergy/status/2064004710877556903", "text": "Oil markets may be underestimating the risks of a prolonged U.S./Israel-Iran stalemate. With the Strait of Hormuz effectively closed and global inventories drawing fast, analysts warn Brent could break above $120-$135/bbl later this summer. #Oil #OOTT #EnergyMarkets \n\nhttps://t.co/eD2sQ8JgSV", "time": "15:20", "author": "OilandEnergy", "author_name": "OilPrice.com", "followers": 95942, "views": 6916, "likes": 95, "replies": 4, "retweets": 10, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 11, "labels": null}, {"id": "2064005263510651104", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2064005263510651104", "text": "BREAKING: In a televised address, Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu says Israel is holding fire for now against Iran.", "time": "15:22", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 51558, "likes": 193, "replies": 15, "retweets": 32, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 11, "labels": null}, {"id": "2064029203318619904", "url": "https://x.com/OilandEnergy/status/2064029203318620517", "text": "The oil market may be far closer to a supply crunch than prices suggest. Analysts warn global inventories are rapidly approaching “operational stress” levels as the Strait of Hormuz disruption continues to drain critical buffer stocks. #Oil #EnergySecurity #OOTT \n\nhttps://t.co/yX1meM9df4", "time": "16:58", "author": "OilandEnergy", "author_name": "OilPrice.com", "followers": 95942, "views": 76464, "likes": 362, "replies": 25, "retweets": 103, "quotes": 9, "bookmarks": 55, "labels": null}, {"id": "2064035077374332928", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2064035077374332977", "text": "US SPR crude inventories fell by ~7.9mb w/w to 349.2mb last week #oott     \nSour down ~4.1mb to 216.0mb   \nSweet down ~3.8mb to 133.2mb https://t.co/raJ3rv6weK", "time": "17:21", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 119640, "views": 68726, "likes": 223, "replies": 14, "retweets": 42, "quotes": 9, "bookmarks": 25, "labels": null}, {"id": "2064058197913076196", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2064058197913076196", "text": "Another large weekly US SPR oil release (technically, an exchange), amounting to ~7.9 million barrels (equal to ~1.1m b/d). \n\nAs of June 5, the SPR held 349.2 million barrels, approaching the low point set during the Biden administration of 346 million barrels (40-year low).", "time": "18:53", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 60611, "likes": 315, "replies": 24, "retweets": 40, "quotes": 7, "bookmarks": 35, "labels": null}, {"id": "2064127684670616064", "url": "https://x.com/TankerTrackers/status/2064127684670615572", "text": "This weekend saw a lot of dark ship-to-ship transfers of oil in the Middle East. It's not Iranian oil. Instead, this is oil coming from Iran's Arab neighbors. Yet another reason why oil isn't $200/barrel right now.\n\n#OOTT #IranWar #Tankers https://t.co/BDUnYErA6e", "time": "23:29", "author": "TankerTrackers", "author_name": "TankerTrackers.com, Inc.", "followers": 226179, "views": 137811, "likes": 605, "replies": 46, "retweets": 160, "quotes": 38, "bookmarks": 91, "labels": null}], "top_authors_by_tweets": [{"username": "staunovo",